CS 480 - Programming Assignment 3
Disk Arm Scheduling Simulator

Team Members:
  - [Name 1] - [Class account, e.g. cssc0000]
  - [Name 2] - [Class account, e.g. cssc0001]

Class account to use for grading: [FILL IN ACCOUNT NAME HERE]

Description:
  This program simulates and compares three disk arm scheduling
  algorithms:
    1. FCFS  (First Come First Served)
    2. SSTF  (Shortest Seek Time First)
    3. SCAN  (Elevator algorithm)

  The program generates a single random sequence of cylinder request
  numbers in the range 0-999, then runs all three algorithms against
  that same sequence, starting from a fixed initial disk arm position
  (cylinder 50). It prints the generated sequence and the total number
  of cylinders each algorithm's arm had to travel to service every
  request.

Files:
  simarm.cpp - Source code implementing the three algorithms and the
               simulation driver.
  Makefile   - Builds the "simarm" executable; also supports "clean".
  README     - This file.

Build:
  make

  This produces an executable named "simarm" in the same directory.

Clean:
  make clean

  This removes the "simarm" executable and any object files.

Run:
  ./simarm <length-of-sequence>

  Example:
    ./simarm 64

  This generates a random sequence of 64 cylinder numbers and prints
  the total head movement for FCFS, SSTF, and SCAN.

Notes:
  - The initial disk arm (head) position is fixed at cylinder 50 for
    all three algorithms so that the results are directly comparable.
  - Valid cylinder numbers range from 0 to 999.
  - The program does not use the system() call.
